TY  - JOUR
T1  - Intergroup Leadership in Organizations: Leading Across Group and Organizational Boundaries
AU  - Hogg, Michael A.
AU  - van Knippenberg, Daan
AU  - Rast, David E.
Y1  - 2012/04/01
PY  - 2012
DA  - 2012/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2010.0221
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2010.0221
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 232
EP  - 255
VL  - 37
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Intergroup leadership?leadership of collaborative performance of different organizational groups or organizations?is associated with unique intergroup challenges that are not addressed by traditional leadership theories. To address this lacuna, we describe a theory of intergroup leadership. Firmly grounded in research on social identity and intergroup relations, the theory proposes that effective intergroup performance rests on the leader's ability to construct an intergroup relational identity. We describe key leadership actions to establish such an identity.
AB  - Intergroup leadership?leadership of collaborative performance of different organizational groups or organizations?is associated with unique intergroup challenges that are not addressed by traditional leadership theories. To address this lacuna, we describe a theory of intergroup leadership. Firmly grounded in research on social identity and intergroup relations, the theory proposes that effective intergroup performance rests on the leader's ability to construct an intergroup relational identity. We describe key leadership actions to establish such an identity.
